The paper discusses adversarial attacks and defenses in machine learning, which are topics that are commonly studied in the subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). However, the paper also touches on information security (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV) as they relate to adversarial attacks. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in both attacking and defending against adversarial attacks. Finally, the paper mentions some extended studies, which could potentially fall under the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
